Hi Oleg, hi rest of the list,

Windows uses the official Nvidia-driver to adjust brightness levels (to
my knowlegde) - brightness is not reduced to the defined level until the
Nvidia's software is loaded at startup (as much as I dislike using
Windows, but it provides the necessary battery time when there's no
power source available). It always takes a couple of seconds, until this
"switch" to a lower level takes place. There are several other
(preinstalled) utilities by Sony, but those are in no way connected to
display-settings (again, as far as I can tell, but I'm pretty sure in
this case).
Thanks for the hint regarding the asl-code, but I've absolutly not the
slightest idea of how to create a program, that could implement
ACPI-specific functions (apart from the fact, that as a student of BA I
lack both skills in asl and most other languages that produce hardcoded
output files ;-)

Thanks for the quick answer

-chris




