0x20 -> horizontal position
0x22 -> horizontal size
0x24 -> adjusts the shape of the screen between something that looks
like this: ) ( and this: ( )
0x30 -> vertical position
0x32 -> vertical size
0x42 -> stretchs/shrinks horizontally the half-bottom of the screen.

That's it, not much useful. I guess there could be some hidden registers
to do the other settings, but who knows?

Thanks,

Alexandre


