I will wait then.  I am subscribed to the freshmeat project, so once I
get the email that the new version is out, I will package it test it and
then submit the package.  If you would like to keep the packaging
metadata (the debian/ directory) under source control with the rest of
the package, we can do that, but I will require CVS access for that.
Email me if you would like to discuss this further.

