Thanks for your report, I think it could be explained by the fact that
Samsung monitors only have 101 discrete possible values for
brightness/contrast (0,1,2...100), so it is clear that you cannot move
from 80.0 to 80.5: the slide will "jump" from 80.0 to 81.0... This
problem should be worse with "Image Lock Fine (Clock Phase)" which has
only 32 possible values.
I'll try to improve this.

> Also, I still saw a few error messages, so I have sent the output of 
> `ddccontrol -p -c -d` again with the new file installed in the db.  The
> output is at the end of the message.

These are not real error messages (except the EDID reading problem, but
it seems the program fixes the problem by reading it again): it only
means that there is no monitor on some I2C buses, which is normal. These
messages are not shown with the latest CVS version unless you add
"-v -v" to the command line.

