Hi ddccontrol developers,

I have a nVidia graphics card connected to two Mitsubishi monitors.

Card: nVidia Corporation NV35 [GeForce FX 5900 Ultra] rev 161

Monitor 2: "Mitsubishi Diamond Plus 92" "Diamondtron NF"
DVI to VGA converter
$ LANG= LC_ALL= ddccontrol -p -c -d > out.txt 2>&1

Monitor 1: "Mitsubishi Diamond Pro 2070sb"
VGA conection
$ LANG= LC_ALL= ddccontrol pci:01:00.0-2 -c -d > out2.txt 2>&1

Is there anyway to get the "Description - Value name" for the controls in the 
above commands?

I've compile this under Debian Stable (with some unstable programs installed) 
and ran into the "ddccontrol-0.2 compile error" reported earlier on this 
mail-list.  My fix was to force Xinerama in the configure script because  it 
wasn't detected and I need it.  Attached is the relevant part of config.log 
which may show why it wasn't detected.

As a suggestion, could you please display a dialog box when a unsupported 
monitor is used with some helpful text.

I've noticed that all supported monitors have Brightness at address 0x10 and 
Contrast at address 0x12.  Could unsupported monitors just have these 
controls?

Thanks,
Paul

