On Thu, 2005-09-22 at 09:08 -0500, Jerry Geis wrote:
> I have a SIS video card...
> lspci shows
> 
> VGA compatible controller: Silicon Integrated Systems [SiS] 661/741/760 
> PCI/AGP VGA Display Adapter
> 
> Will this work with ddccontrol?

Probably not.
You may try to load the sisfb kernel module (you may have to recompile
your kernel to enable it), but as far as I can see in the kernel code,
there is no support for I2C busses access using /dev/i2c-* devices.

BTW, I'm not sure your TV supports DDC/CI. I could be sure if you could
provide the output of "ddccontrol -p -c -d" on your laptop (nVidia
card).

Best regards,

Nicolas



