> i recently updated ddccontrol to 0.2, and ran gddccontrol. everything
> went fine fine except for this error message: "Error while opening
> ddccontrol home directory.: No such file or directory".
> 
> i created ~/.ddccontrol/profiles and the message disappeared.
> 
> in lib/profile.c, as ddcci_create_profiledir is called only upon
> creation of a profile, it can happen that the profile dir does not exist
> when ddcci_get_all_profiles is called, i think this case should not
> generate an error (maybe just call ddcci_create_profiledir). i'm
