Hi,
Suggested by DDCcontrol documentatian page: Appendix A, I would like to 
present my "expireince" with ddccontrol with LCD monitor Samsung 
SyncMaster 171P.

  Hardware
 ==========
Motherboard: ABIT NF7S (NForce2 chipset)
Graph. Carh: Radeon 9200 (D-SUB and DVI outputs)

  Software
 ==========
Kernel: 2.6.14 - vanilla; configured and build by me (i2c-dev and 
        radeonfb as modules)
DDCcontrol: ver. 0.2 

DDCcontrol has found my monitor as DDC/CI supported only by _analog_ 
output, but not recognized transfered data: "corrupted data". 
Digitally(DVI)-connected monitor is found but as NOT DDC/CI compatible.
Full output of the ddccontrol, you may found:

for analog:
http://www.cbk.waw.pl/~radek/DDCcontrol/Samsung_SyncMaster171p_analog.txt

for digital:
http://www.cbk.waw.pl/~radek/DDCcontrol/Samsung_SyncMaster171p_dvi.txt

I would like to note, that ddccontrol with kernel 2.4.31 (with the 
newest lm_sensors/i2c packages) has not found my monitor.

Ciao,
Radek Marcinkowski 


