Samsung 193Pplus has two connection types: D-sub (VGA) and DVI. It presents 
two identities: SAM0198 for D-sub and SAM0199 for DVI.
This means that if you connect your monitor through D-sub, the SAM0198.xml 
file is sufficient. But if you connect this monitor ONLY through DVI, you 
need a file called SAM0199.xml, with this content:

<?xml version="1.0"?>
<!---The Samsung 193P+ seems to be identical to 173P and 193P -->
<monitor include="SAM00D3" name="Samsung SyncMaster 193P Plus (DVI)"/>

Emil

