Hi,

As I promissed, I have made tests of ddccontrol with Samsung SyncMaster 
171P, an old LCD model.

First of all I would like to confirm that it works only by D-SUB (analog) 
connector and not work by DVI -- I mean: ddccontrol does not work!, 
monitor works on both :)

I did some corrrection in corresponding xml file:
1. replaced _contrast_ with _brightness_
2. add two controls for Image Lock: Fine/Coarse

!IMPORTANT! 
3. I've found, that for: _hpos_ and _vpos_ maximal value are 100s instead 
of found by "ddccontrol -p -c -d" 255s:
I mean: ddccontrol shows for example:
  Control 0x20: +/42/255
  Control 0x30: +/31/255
but OSD tunning allows only for 100 maximal value -- when position of 
hpos is maxial on OSD, then 'ddccontrol -r 0x20 pci:02:00.0-0' shows:
  Control 0x20: +/100/255
I did not decide to check what happend when I will do:
# ddccontrol -r 0x20 -w 101 pci:02:00.0-0

Note:
Sometimes my LCD is going to _lock_ some option in OSD menu (D-SUB) - it 
should not happend. I've googled that pressing together on three buttons:
  "-" + "+" + "Menu"
unlocks OSD options - it may be useful for some users.

Finnaly, my version of xml file:

=======SAM001D.xml===========
<?xml version="1.0"?>
<!--- Samsung SyncMaster 171P has some primitive DDC/CI support (no caps, 
      only a few controls) -->
<monitor name="Samsung SyncMaster 171P (VGA)" init="standard" caps="">
	<controls>
		<control id="contrast"   address="0x10"/> <!-- corrected, 
		was: "brightness" -->
		<control id="brightness" address="0x12"/> <!-- corrected, 
		was: "contrast" -->
		<control id="red"        address="0x16"/>
		<control id="green"      address="0x18"/>
		<control id="blue"       address="0x1a"/>
		
		<control id="hpos"       address="0x20"/> <!-- max should 
		be 100 instead of 255 
		(as recognised by ddccontrol -p -c -d) -->
		<control id="vpos"       address="0x30"/> <!-- max should 
		be 100 instead of 255 
		(as recognised by ddccontrol -p -c -d) -->

<!-- The following two controls corresponds to menu 
     "Image Lock: Fine/Coarse", they change left-right position and size 
     of the screen with some narrow distorteded areas from top to bottom 
-->
		<control id="fine"       address="0xd0"/> <!-- was: 
		Control 0xd0: +/174/255 [???]-->
		<control id="coarse"     address="0xd2"/> <!-- was: 
		Control 0xd2: +/60/120 [???]-->

		<!-- Still unknown -->
		<!--- Control 0xdc: +/15/150 [???] -->
		<!--- Control 0xdd: +/31/150 [???] -->
		<!--- Control 0xde: +/16/150 [???] -->
		<!--- Control 0xe4: +/163/63 [???] -->
		<!--- Control 0xe6: +/163/63 [???] -->
		<!--- Control 0xe8: +/165/63 [???] -->
	</controls>
</monitor>
========End of SAM001D.xml ===========

Radek


