Hi Radek,

On Mon, 2005-11-21 at 11:12 +0100, Radoslaw Marcinkowski wrote:
> Hi,
> 
> As I promissed, I have made tests of ddccontrol with Samsung SyncMaster 
> 171P, an old LCD model.
> 
> First of all I would like to confirm that it works only by D-SUB (analog) 
> connector and not work by DVI -- I mean: ddccontrol does not work!, 
> monitor works on both :)
> 
> I did some corrrection in corresponding xml file:
> 1. replaced _contrast_ with _brightness_

I reverted this change. In fact constrast and brightness have different
meanings on LCDs and CRTs, and in ddccontrol-db, brightness is always on
adress 0x10, and contrast on 0x12.

> 2. add two controls for Image Lock: Fine/Coarse

Fine.

> !IMPORTANT! 
> 3. I've found, that for: _hpos_ and _vpos_ maximal value are 100s instead 
> of found by "ddccontrol -p -c -d" 255s:
> I mean: ddccontrol shows for example:
>   Control 0x20: +/42/255
>   Control 0x30: +/31/255
> but OSD tunning allows only for 100 maximal value -- when position of 
> hpos is maxial on OSD, then 'ddccontrol -r 0x20 pci:02:00.0-0' shows:
>   Control 0x20: +/100/255
> I did not decide to check what happend when I will do:
> # ddccontrol -r 0x20 -w 101 pci:02:00.0-0

Ok... I don't think writing 101 to these control would break anything...
I will think about adding a "max" attribute for control elements in
monitor files.

> Note:
> Sometimes my LCD is going to _lock_ some option in OSD menu (D-SUB) - it 
> should not happend. I've googled that pressing together on three buttons:
>   "-" + "+" + "Menu"
> unlocks OSD options - it may be useful for some users.

Really strange...

> Finnaly, my version of xml file:

Thanks.

Best regards,

Nicolas



