Hi!

I would like to inform about success with ddccontrol and Samsung 770p.

Hardware: Radeon 9200 SE (digital and analog output), motherboard MSI KT6 
Delta

Software: kernel 2.6.12-10-k7 (ubuntu 5.10), fglrx 8.19.10, ddccontrol 
0.3.1 (from cvs), db-ddcontrol - from cvs.

Ddccontrol used pci to talk with monitor.
Samsung 770p works with settings for Samsung 970p. Ddccontrol needs two 
files to work with 770p - SAM01B3.xml (analog connection) and 
SAM01B4.xml (digital) with content:

<?xml version="1.0"?>
<monitor include="SAM00D3" name="Samsung SyncMaster 770P"/>

Ddccontrol and lspci outputs:
http://vega.umcs.lublin.pl/~drach/ddc_lspci.txt

-- 
Best regards
Mateusz Drach


