Probably the problem is related to dpkg. 
For compiling the sources I use dpkg-buildpackage that runs configure,
make and make install and creates a .deb Debian package. Then I install
the package with my package manager. I use this method to keep track of
all the files on my system.

The permission is set wrong during the creation of the deb file, but
it's the first time that I have such problems.

